---
title: "init-project — Analyze + Create CLAUDE.md + Modules + Settings + Report"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Claude
    participant FS as File System
    participant Glob as Glob Tool
    participant MD as module-documenter<br/>subagent (fan-out)

    note over Claude,FS: Analyze architecture
    Claude->>FS: Scan headers/exports
    FS-->>Claude: Public interfaces
    Claude->>Claude: Map dependencies +<br/>communication patterns

    note over Claude,FS: Create CLAUDE.md
    Claude->>Claude: Build compact overview<br/>(under 200 lines, @path imports)
    Claude->>FS: Write CLAUDE.md
    FS-->>Claude: OK

    Claude->>User: CLAUDE.md created (N lines)<br/>Review? Test build commands?
    User-->>Claude: Approve or request edits

    note over Claude,User: Phase: Scaffold base rules
    Claude->>User: Scaffold starter rules for <stack>?<br/>[1] code-style    — naming, file layout, formatter config<br/>[2] testing       — test location, runner, coverage approach<br/>[3] architecture  — module boundaries + allowed imports<br/>[4] api-design    — REST/gRPC/event contract conventions<br/>[5] security      — forbidden patterns, auth requirements<br/>[A] All of the above<br/>[N] None — I'll add rules manually later
    User-->>Claude: selection (numbers / A / N)

    loop For each selected rule
        Claude->>Claude: Generate rule body — stack-aware:<br/>paths: scoped to matching files,<br/>conventions from detected formatter/linter,<br/>examples from actual project structure
        Claude->>FS: Write .claude/rules/<name>.md
        FS-->>Claude: OK
    end

    note over Claude,MD: Create module CLAUDE.md files (fan-out)
    Claude->>Claude: Filter modules — skip trivial (<5 files)
    Claude->>Claude: TodoWrite — one checkbox per non-trivial module:<br/>☐ module-a/CLAUDE.md<br/>☐ module-b/CLAUDE.md<br/>☐ ...
    Note right of Claude: Deep scan + generation moved out of<br/>main context — one subagent per module<br/>runs in parallel (per rules/fan-out cap)

    par For each non-trivial module (parallel fan-out)
        Claude->>MD: Invoke with<br/>{module_path, project_root,<br/>stack_summary, project_type,<br/>hub_module_name, rpc_layer_hint,<br/>conventions_summary}
        Note right of MD: Subagent reads public interface,<br/>deps, reverse-deps, sub-structure,<br/>patterns — in its OWN context
        MD-->>Claude: {summary_row (YAML),<br/>claude_md_content (markdown body)}
    end

    Claude->>Claude: Aggregate summary_rows<br/>→ module-table for the dashboard<br/>→ drop entries where content = "SKIP"

    loop For each non-SKIP content (batch write)
        Claude->>FS: Write module/CLAUDE.md<br/>(verbatim from subagent output)
        FS-->>Claude: OK
        Claude->>Claude: TodoUpdate — ☑ module/CLAUDE.md
    end

    Claude->>User: Created N module CLAUDE.md<br/>files (skipped M trivial)

    note over Claude,FS: Update settings
    Claude->>FS: Update .claude/settings.json<br/>(stack-specific permissions)
    FS-->>Claude: OK

    note over Claude,FS: Report — write file + show dashboard
    Claude->>Claude: END_TS = date +%s<br/>wall_clock_sec = END_TS - START_TS
    Claude->>FS: Collect artefact list<br/>(wc -l on each created file)
    FS-->>Claude: Paths + line counts
    Claude->>FS: Write .claude/state/reports/<br/>init-project-DISPLAY_TS.md<br/>(per rules/report-format.md —<br/>first line machine-diff comment,<br/>body with Summary/Phase Timings/<br/>Artefacts/Next-step)
    FS-->>Claude: Report saved

    Claude->>User: Dashboard with stats<br/>(Type, Stack, Duration, CLAUDE.md,<br/>Modules, Settings, Report path)<br/>+ next steps:<br/>/create-docs rule ...<br/>/create-mermaid sequence ...

    opt has_frontend flag set (from Pass 2b)
        Claude->>User: Frontend detected at candidate(s)<br/>Run /analyze-frontend now? [y/n/d]
        alt User accepts (y)
            Claude->>Claude: Invoke /claude-docs-creator:analyze-frontend<br/>(passes first candidate path as argument)
            Note right of Claude: Analysis runs inline —<br/>generates frontend-specific<br/>rules + docs + data-flow diagram
        else User declines (n or d)
            Claude->>Claude: Append Notes entry to run report:<br/>"Frontend(s) detected at X but<br/>/analyze-frontend declined —<br/>user can run it later"
        end
    end
